how to add affiliate links in WordPress? If you&#8217;ve got a blog with a decent number of daily visitors, you can earn plenty of referral income with affiliate marketing; but you have to be smart when choosing the tools to turn your blog into a successful affiliate marketing site. In this article, well show [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-affiliate-links-in-wordpress-and-properly-track-them/\">How to Add Affiliate Links in WordPress (and Properly Track Them)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:16932:\"<p>Wondering how to add affiliate links in WordPress? If you&#8217;ve got a blog with a decent number of daily visitors, you can earn plenty of referral income with affiliate marketing; but you have to be smart when choosing the tools to turn your blog into a successful affiliate marketing site.</p>\n<p>In this article, well show you how to add and organize affiliate links in WordPress using <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ThirstyAffiliates</a>. Then, in the last section of the article, well show how to properly track your affiliate links to grow your affiliate marketing.</p>\n<h3>Using ThirstyAffiliates to Add and Organize Affiliate Links in WordPress</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ThirstyAffiliates</a> is the best affiliate management and cloaking plugin for WordPress. It helps you to cloak your affiliate links and add them into your blog posts with ease. You can also organize your affiliate links by categories and add automatic keywords so that affiliate management in WordPress will be really easy.</p>\n<p>In general, affiliate links are long and look ugly that are hard to remember. Most affiliate links look like this:</p>\n<p>http://example.com/products/?product_id=123&#038;affiliate_id</p>\n<p>ThirstyAffiliates helps you to cloak such affiliate links to make them short and branded URLs as shown below:</p>\n<p>http://www.yoursite.com/recommends/productname</p>\n<p>As you grow as an affiliate marketer, youre likely to use the same affiliate link on tons of different blog posts. With ThirstyAffiliates, you can store all your affiliate links in one place in your WordPress backend and use them whenever you need. Plus, it has a fully functional search option to help you search for links by the link title.</p>\n<p>In addition to proper management of affiliate links, cloaking also helps you to prevent commission theft. By using cloaked links, you can add an additional layer of click tracking to ensure you are getting paid for every sale you refer.</p>\n<p>Now, lets go ahead and see how to add affiliate links in WordPress step-by-step.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Install ThirstyAffiliates and Configure Settings</h3>\n<p>First of all, go to the<a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ThirstyAffiliates</a> website and buy a subscription plan. Then, go ahead and install the plugin in WordPress.</p>\n<p>After the plugin is activated on your site, go to <strong>ThirstyAffiliates  Settings</strong> from your WordPress dashboard. This will open the <strong>General</strong> tab in ThirstyAffiliate Settings.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155953\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-general-settings.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-general-settings\" width=\"560\" height=\"290\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-general-settings.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-general-settings-300x155.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, you can review all the settings and change the settings if you want to. At the end, dont forget to click the<strong>Save Changes</strong> button.</p>\n<p>Second tab in ThirstyAffiliates settings is <strong>Link Appearance</strong>. It allows you to configure settings that affect the behavior and appearance or your affiliate links. You can configure some of the important settings from there.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155954\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings\" width=\"560\" height=\"312\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings-300x167.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>First, you can choose a link prefix that will be used in your cloaked links before your affiliate ID. The plugin, by default, has <strong>/recommends/</strong> set up which you can replace with any of the available prefixes such as recommends, fly, proceed, goto, etc. Also, you can choose <strong>custom</strong> to add a new prefix.</p>\n<p>Next, you can choose whether you want to show a link category in your affiliate URL or not. Then, you can choose link redirect type, use no follow on links, and open links in new window.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155955\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings-2.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings-2\" width=\"560\" height=\"510\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings-2.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-appearance-settings-2-300x273.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Review all the settings, make the necessary changes, and then, click <strong>Save Changes</strong> button.</p>\n<p>The third tab in ThirstAffiliates Settings is <strong>Modules</strong>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155956\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-module-settings.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-module-settings\" width=\"560\" height=\"422\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-module-settings.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-module-settings-300x226.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>From this page, you can enable ThirstyAffiliates statistics that collects data about your users who click your affiliate links. If it&#8217;s enabled, it shows reports; however, the module slows down your site. So we recommend using <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> for tracking your affiliate links.</p>\n<p>The <strong>Link Fixer</strong> will help you to fix any outdated / broken affiliate links on your site. <strong>Uncloak Links</strong> will allow you to uncloak specific links or categories to make it compatible with some affiliate programs with stricter terms (such as Amazon Associates).</p>\n<p>The fourth tab <strong>Import/Export</strong> provides you with options to export ThirstyAffiliates settings and import settings from other WordPress sites.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155957\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-import-export-settings.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-import-export-settings\" width=\"560\" height=\"450\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-import-export-settings.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-import-export-settings-300x241.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>After you choose the options, make sure to click the<strong>Save Changes</strong> button.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Add Link Categories and New Affiliate Links</h3>\n<p>After youve configured the settings, youre now ready to create link categories.</p>\n<p>To add link categories, go to <strong>ThirstyAffiliates  Link Categories</strong> from your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155958\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-categories.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-link-categories\" width=\"560\" height=\"379\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-categories.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-link-categories-300x203.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, give a name to your new link category, set a slug, and add a description. Then, click the <strong>Add New Category</strong> button.</p>\n<p>After you create sufficient categories for your links, you can go ahead and add your links.</p>\n<p>To add a new affiliate link, youll need to go to <strong>ThirstyAffiliates  New Affiliate Link</strong> from your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p>Now, you can easily add affiliate links.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155959\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates.jpg\" alt=\"add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates\" width=\"560\" height=\"325\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates-300x174.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>In the first field, give a name to your link. You can use the products name so that itll be easy to search and embed in posts.</p>\n<p>Next, youll need to add the original affiliate link in the <strong>Destination URL</strong> field.</p>\n<p>Then, you can attach images as well. This is useful for website owners who want to display affiliate links with images in sidebars. You can also add autolink keywords for your affiliate link if youre using ThirstyAffiliates&#8217; paid version.</p>\n<p>In the right panel, you can choose a link category. As you scroll down, you can find link options. Youll see the options as you configured in the <strong>Link Appearance</strong> as we discussed above. Review them, and click the<strong>Save Link</strong> button.</p>\n<p>Thats it. Now, you can repeat the same process to add more affiliate links.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: Adding Affiliate Links in WordPress Posts and Pages</h3>\n<p>Once youve added affiliate links in <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ThirstyAffiliates</a>, now you can add the cloaked affiliate links in your posts and pages.</p>\n<p>ThirstyAffiliates makes the process of adding links really easy as it adds an icon in your post editor to embed affiliate links.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155960\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/embed-affiliate-link-in-post.jpg\" alt=\"embed-affiliate-link-in-post\" width=\"560\" height=\"261\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/embed-affiliate-link-in-post.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/embed-affiliate-link-in-post-300x140.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>As you click on the link, itll open the search box where you can type your affiliate link name. Then, you can select and add on your post.</p>\n<p>It also has another icon,<strong>Quick Add Affiliate Link</strong>, that you can use to add a new affiliate link and embed it in your post.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155961\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-icon.jpg\" alt=\"quck-add-affiliate-link-icon\" width=\"560\" height=\"195\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-icon.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-icon-300x104.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>When you click on the icon, a popup box will appear. You can add a new affiliate link and then embed it in the post.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155962\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates.jpg\" alt=\"quck-add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates\" width=\"560\" height=\"300\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/quck-add-affiliate-link-thirstyaffiliates-300x161.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Thats it. Now, you can publish your post and check if your affiliate links are working.</p>\n<h3>How to Properly Track Your Affiliate Links</h3>\n<p>ThirstyAffilites comes with a Statistics module that tracks the affiliate clicks on your site; however, itll slow down your website because it uses your website&#8217;s resources.</p>\n<p>So, we recommend you use <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> to track your affiliate links. Since it uses event-based tracking from Google Analytics, it wont affect your website speed. Plus, the reports from Google Analytics are more reliable than any other services.</p>\n<p>Now, lets see how to enable affiliate tracking in WordPress using MonsterInsghts.</p>\n<h3>Affiliate Links Tracking with MonsterInsights</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> makes affiliate links tracking so simple that itll take just a few clicks to complete the setup process.</p>\n<p>Navigate to <strong>Insights  Settings</strong> from your WordPress dashboard and then click on the <strong>Tracking</strong> tab at the top of the page. Then, go to the <strong>Affiliate Links</strong> tab in the left taskbar.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-108939\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/affiliate-link-tracking.jpg\" alt=\"affiliate link tracking in wordpress\" width=\"560\" height=\"578\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/affiliate-link-tracking.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/affiliate-link-tracking-291x300.jpg 291w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>There, youll see 2 fields:</p>\n<p><strong>i) Set path for internal links to track as outbound links:</strong></p>\n<p>If youre using an affiliate management plugin like <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ThirstyAffiliates</a>, your affiliate links will look like:</p>\n<p>http://example.com/recommends/your-affiliate-link</p>\n<p>In the above example, your affiliate link begins with /recommends/.</p>\n<p>You can simply copy the prefix <strong>/recommends/</strong> on this field, so Google Analytics can identify which internal links are affiliate links. If you use multiple prefixes, you can separate them with a comma: /recommends/,/out/.</p>\n<p><strong>ii) Label for those links:</strong></p>\n<p>The label in your Google Analytics report lets you identify where the click came from. For example, you can add a label <strong>aff</strong> to your affiliate links.</p>\n<p>After you complete these 2 fields, click <strong>Save Changes</strong>.</p>\n<p>Thats it. Youre done with affiliate links tracking setup.</p>\n<p>Now, you can view the reports by visiting <strong> Insights  Reports  Publishers</strong> from your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155898\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/affiliate-link-tracking-report-monsterinsights.jpg\" alt=\"affiliate-link-tracking-report-monsterinsights\" width=\"560\" height=\"600\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/affiliate-link-tracking-report-monsterinsights.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/affiliate-link-tracking-report-monsterinsights-280x300.jpg 280w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>You can always click the <strong>View All Affiliate Links Report</strong> to view more reports in Google Analytics.</p>\n<p>If you want detailed instructions, heres our complete guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-set-up-affiliate-link-tracking-in-wordpress/\">setting up affiliate links tracking</a>.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you to learn how to add affiliate links in WordPress and to properly track them.</p>\n<p>You might also want to check out our guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-check-the-number-of-visitors-for-your-wordpress-site/\">how to check the number of visitors for your WordPress site</a>.</p>\n<p>Also, dont forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more Google Analytics tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-affiliate-links-in-wordpress-and-properly-track-them/\">How to Add Affiliate Links in WordPress (and Properly Track Them)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:101:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-add-affiliate-links-in-wordpress-and-properly-track-them/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:7;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:54:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:73:\"How to See Your Least Performing WordPress Pages (3 Tips to Improve Them)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:223:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-see-your-least-performing-wordpress-pages-and-tips-to-improve-them/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=how-to-see-your-least-performing-wordpress-pages-and-tips-to-improve-them\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:114:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-see-your-least-performing-wordpress-pages-and-tips-to-improve-them/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 03 Sep 2018 13:15:38 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:5:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Tutorials\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:11:\"bounce rate\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:23:\"MonsterInsights Reports\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"tracking least performing pages\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:4;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:21:\"the exit pages report\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=155552\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:662:\"<p>Do you want to see your least performing WordPress pages? If youre serious about your business growth, identifying your least performing pages can help you a lot as youll know which pages to focus on and optimize. With Google Analytics, you can track the performance of all your WordPress pages and find out both the [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-see-your-least-performing-wordpress-pages-and-tips-to-improve-them/\">How to See Your Least Performing WordPress Pages (3 Tips to Improve Them)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:12170:\"<p>Do you want to see your least performing WordPress pages? If youre serious about your business growth, identifying your least performing pages can help you a lot as youll know which pages to focus on and optimize. With Google Analytics, you can track the performance of all your WordPress pages and find out both the highest converting and least performing pages.</p>\n<p>In this article, well show you how to see your least performing WordPress pages. And, well also share 3 best tips to improve them.</p>\n<h3>Why Track Your Least Performing WordPress Pages?</h3>\n<p>When we always focus our attention on the best, we miss out on the greater opportunities the least performing pages can offer. Sometimes, we can make really good conversions out of the least performing pages with little improvements.</p>\n<p>When you know which pages are least performing, you can analyze why those pages arent able to capture the users attention and then make changes to optimize them.</p>\n<p>Among several Google Analytics factors, bounce rates are important to find out how engaging your pages are. If a page has a higher bounce rate, it means the page is less engaging.</p>\n<p>But sometimes bounce rates can be high due to external factors like referrer spam (backlinks from the malicious websites). If your pages have a 100% bounce rate, you can suspect referrer spam. In case you detected spam, you can remove them and avoid any harm it can cause.</p>\n<p>Now, lets see how to view your least performing WordPress pages.</p>\n<h3>Step 1: Set Up Google Analytics in Your WordPress Site</h3>\n<p>Google Analytics is the most reliable website analytics tool. It helps you to track all the important data about your website visitors and their interactions on your site. With Google Analytics, you can track the overall bounce rate for your entire site as well as for individual pages; however, the setup process is a bit tricky for beginners.</p>\n<p>So, we recommend you use the<a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. It helps you set up Google Analytics for WordPress very easily. Also, it simplifies tracking advanced metrics such as form and eCommerce conversions, affiliate links, etc.</p>\n<p>First of all, youll need to install MonsterInsights in WordPress and then set up Google Analytics. Using this plugin, you can set up Google Analytics in WordPress with just a few clicks.</p>\n<p>If you want detailed instructions, heres our step-by-step guide to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\">setting up Google Analytics in WordPress</a>.</p>\n<h3>Step 2: Track Your Site&#8217;s Bounce Rates</h3>\n<p>After the setup process is complete, you can view your sites overview report right in your WordPress dashboard with the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/introducing-google-analytics-dashboard-widget-for-monsterinsights/\">MonsterInsights dashboard widget</a>.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155980\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/mi-dashboard-widget-report-bounce-rate.jpg\" alt=\"mi-dashboard-widget-report-bounce-rate\" width=\"560\" height=\"438\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/mi-dashboard-widget-report-bounce-rate.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/mi-dashboard-widget-report-bounce-rate-300x235.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>As you can see in the screenshot above, youll see your site&#8217;s bounce rate right in the overview report. Bounce rate is one of the key measures to find out your site&#8217;s engagement.</p>\n<p>If you don&#8217;t know what <a href=\"https://support.google.com/analytics/answer/1009409?hl=en&amp;ref_topic=6156780\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">bounce rate</a> is, it&#8217;s the percentage of all sessions with only page pageview and a single request. For example, if a user opens a page in your site, and exits without clicking on any buttons or links (or without triggering a request to Analytics server), it&#8217;s called a bounce.</p>\n<p>High bounce rates aren&#8217;t always bad, but it depends on the type of a site you have. If your site is a single page site with no internal pages or posts, high bounce rate is quite normal.</p>\n<p>But if you&#8217;ve got plenty of links in your pages for users to click, high bounce rate means low user engagement for your pages.</p>\n<p>Now, let&#8217;s see how to view bounce rate for your pages.</p>\n<p>First, youll need to navigate to <strong>MonsterInsights  Reports</strong> from your WordPress admin panel. At first, youll see the overview report that youve already viewed on the dashboard widget. So, click on the<strong>Publishers</strong> tab on the top, and then youll see your top landing pages with their bounce rate.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-156003\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/bounce-rate-top-landing-pages.jpg\" alt=\"bounce-rate-top-landing-pages\" width=\"560\" height=\"660\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/bounce-rate-top-landing-pages.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/bounce-rate-top-landing-pages-255x300.jpg 255w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>MonsterInsights will show you the top 50 landing pages in your site. If you want to view more than that, you can click <strong>View Full Top Landing Pages Report</strong>.</p>\n<p>This will redirect you to <strong>Analytics  Behavior  Site Content  Landing Pages</strong> in your Google Analytics account.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-156004\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/ga-bounce-rate-top-landing-pages.jpg\" alt=\"ga-bounce-rate-top-landing-pages\" width=\"560\" height=\"437\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/ga-bounce-rate-top-landing-pages.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/ga-bounce-rate-top-landing-pages-300x234.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>You can view bounce rate for each of your landing pages from there as well.</p>\n<h3>Step 3: View Your Top Exit Pages</h3>\n<p>Another report thatll show you the least performing pages in WordPress is the <strong>Top Exit Pages</strong>. Top exit pages are the pages where most of your users click the exit button. So, we can consider these page as least performing pages.</p>\n<p>To view your top exit pages, youll need open the <strong>Publishers</strong> report again. Go to <strong>Insights  Reports  Publishers</strong> from your WordPress admin panel.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-156005\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/top-exit-pages-mi-publishers-report.jpg\" alt=\"top-exit-pages-mi-publishers-report\" width=\"560\" height=\"498\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/top-exit-pages-mi-publishers-report.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/top-exit-pages-mi-publishers-report-300x267.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>To view detailed reports, you can click <strong>View Full Top Exit Pages Report</strong>. It&#8217;ll redirect you to <strong>Analytics  Behavior  Site Content  Exit Pages</strong> in Google Analytics.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-156025\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/ga-top-exit-pages.jpg\" alt=\"ga-top-exit-pages\" width=\"560\" height=\"450\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/ga-top-exit-pages.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/ga-top-exit-pages-300x241.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Now, lets go ahead and see how to improve them.</p>\n<h3>3 Best Tips to Improve Your Least Performing WordPress Pages</h3>\n<p>Now, that you know your least converting pages, you probably want to know how to improve them. Below are the 3 best tips to improve your least converting pages.</p>\n<h4>1. Add Optin Forms</h4>\n<p>If your webpages are failing to grab users attentions, adding optin forms can help you greatly to improve the conversion rates. You can capture the abandoning visitors into email subscribers and also send them to other important links in your site.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">OptinMonster</a> is a great tool for lead generation and conversion optimization. You can use it as a plugin on your WordPress site.</p>\n<p>OptinMonster comes with signature <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/exit-intent/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Exit-Intent technology</a> that allows you to convert abandoning visitors into subscribers and customers.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-156021\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/optinmonster-exit-intent-technology.gif\" alt=\"optinmonster-exit-intent-technology\" width=\"600\" height=\"434\" /></p>\n<p>It detects user behavior and prompts them with a targeted campaign at the precise moment they attempt to leave.</p>\n<h4>2. Add Forms and Live Chat to Facilitate User Interaction</h4>\n<p>Second, you can make your pages more interactive by adding forms and live chat options.</p>\n<p>To add forms, you can use <a href=\"https://wpforms.com/\">WPForms</a>. Its the most user-friendly WordPress form plugin that lets you add forms of all types including simple contact forms, survey, and feedback forms, order forms, payment forms, etc. using its simple drag and drop interface.</p>\n<p>Next, you can make your webpages more interactive by adding live chat. Most of the time, users simply exit your page because they dont find anything to do on your site. Sometimes, they may want to talk with you but with no clue, they may close your site. So, adding a live chat can help to make your site more engaging.</p>\n<p>To add live chat in your WordPress site with ease, you can use a live chat software like <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/livechat/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">LiveChat</a>.</p>\n<h4>3. Optimize Your Content to Make it Visually Impressive</h4>\n<p>Another very effective tip for improving your site is to make your page visually impressive.</p>\n<p>For example, you have published a tutorial article on your site, just like this one. Imagine, there are no paragraphs separated, no headings, no images, no buttons, no sidebars but the text content is the same. Will a user bother to read the content? Probably not. A page like that is super boring!</p>\n<p>Now think of that same content, structured well with proper headings, paragraphs separated, images, and call to action buttons. Therere high chances the visitor will read your content and take the action you want them to do.</p>\n<p>If you want more tips to build an effective landing page in WordPress, here&#8217;s our <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-structure-an-effective-landing-page-that-converts/\">complete guide for beginners</a>.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you to learn how to track links and button clicks in WordPress using Google Analytics.</p>\n<p>You might also want to check out our guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/4-ways-to-boost-your-seo-rankings-with-google-analytics/\">4 ways to boost your SEO rankings with Google Analytics</a>.</p>\n<p>Also, dont forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more Google Analytics tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-see-your-least-performing-wordpress-pages-and-tips-to-improve-them/\">How to See Your Least Performing WordPress Pages (3 Tips to Improve Them)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:111:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-see-your-least-performing-wordpress-pages-and-tips-to-improve-them/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:8;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:69:\"22 Must Have WordPress Plugins and Tools for Business Websites (2018)\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:195:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/must-have-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-business-websites/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=must-have-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-business-websites\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:100:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/must-have-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-business-websites/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Thu, 30 Aug 2018 13:15:01 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"grow your business website\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:26:\"best plugins for WordPress\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:32:\"best WordPress plugins and tools\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=155222\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:646:\"<p>Want to add more power to your business website? If youre using WordPress as your website platform, you can find thousands of plugins and tools on the market to boost your business site. Unfortunately, having so many options can feel overwhelming, and cause you to stop searching before you even begin. We feel your pain. [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/must-have-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-business-websites/\">22 Must Have WordPress Plugins and Tools for Business Websites (2018)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35178:\"<p>Want to add more power to your business website? If youre using WordPress as your website platform, you can find thousands of plugins and tools on the market to boost your business site.</p>\n<p>Unfortunately, having so many options can feel overwhelming, and cause you to stop searching before you even begin. We feel your pain. That&#8217;s why weve handpicked 22 must-have plugins and tools for business websites in 2018.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">1. MonsterInsights</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\"><img src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress\" width=\"620\" height=\"250\" class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157422\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress-300x121.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"> MonsterInsights</a> is the best and most user-friendly Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. It helps you to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-properly-setup-google-analytics-in-wordpress/\">install Google Analytics in WordPress easily</a> and provides you with detailed reports about your website&#8217;s traffic and visitor interactions on your site. Then, you can analyze the reports and create informed strategies to grow your business.</p>\n<p>The plugin simplifies the whole process of using Google Analytics so anyone can integrate the powerful Google Analytics service with WordPress and track important website metrics. It helps you to find out who your website visitors are by their age, gender, interests, location, what they do on your site, and much more.</p>\n<p>Plus, you can track advanced metrics like eCommerce conversions, forms, file downloads, etc. with just a few clicks by using its <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addons/\">powerful addons</a>.</p>\n<p>Another benefit of using MonsterInsights is that its available in both the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/google-analytics-for-wordpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">free</a> and premium versions, so you have the option to try the free version first before making a purchase.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">2. WPForms</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-151941\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/wpforms-best-wp-contact-form-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"wpforms-best-wp-contact-form-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/wpforms-best-wp-contact-form-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/07/wpforms-best-wp-contact-form-plugin-300x150.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Contact forms are a must-have for any type of website. By adding a contact form on your website, you can facilitate secure and easy communication with your website visitors.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WPForms</a> is the best WordPress contact form plugin on the market. This amazing plugin helps you to create online forms easily and quickly. It comes with an intuitive drag and drop form builder that allows you to create simple to complex WordPress forms such as email subscription forms, order forms, payment forms, etc. with just a few clicks of your mouse. Youll find a sample template for each type of form, so itll be really easy to get started.</p>\n<p>Once youve created the forms, you can embed them easily on your site. The plugin provides an<strong>Add Form</strong> button in your post editor area, so you can simply click on that to select and insert a form. If you want to add your forms in your site&#8217;s sidebars or any widget-ready area, you can use the WPForms widget. In the nutshell, its the most beginner-friendly WordPress form plugin. You can also use the <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wpforms-lite/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">free version</a> of the plugin for general forms.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">3. OptinMonster</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155241\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/optinmonster-conversion-optimization-software.jpg\" alt=\"optinmonster-conversion-optimization-software\" width=\"560\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/optinmonster-conversion-optimization-software.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/optinmonster-conversion-optimization-software-300x139.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">OptinMonster</a> is the most popular conversion optimization software available. It helps you to grow your email list and boost site conversions. Using this plugin, you can create high-converting email optin forms and display them strategically on your site.</p>\n<p>OptinMonster&#8217;s signature <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/features/exit-intent/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Exit-Intent technology</a> is a great feature that helps you convert your abandoning visitors into subscribers. It detects the user&#8217;s behavior and prompts them with a targeted campaign exactly when the user is about to exit your site. This is why OptinMonster is highly efficient at collecting more leads.</p>\n<p>Furthermore, it offers over 60 beautiful pre-made templates that are proven to convert. You can pick one of them, personalize it, and use on your site. And, you can easily connect it with auto responders and start sending emails once you connect your e-mail list.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"> 4. Constant Contact</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155273\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/constant-contact.jpg\" alt=\"constant-contact\" width=\"560\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/constant-contact.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/constant-contact-300x139.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/constant-contact/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Constant Contact</a> is one of most popular email marketing services available, and for good reason. It allows you to create beautiful custom emails easily and send them to your email subscribers. Constant Contact makes powerful email marketing effortless and quick for beginners.</p>\n<p>With Constant Contact, you can get over 100 beautifully-designed email templates that you can customize with your logo, images, and colors. It has an intuitive drag and drop interface for adding blocks and editing the design of the email templates.</p>\n<p>It works well with lead generation plugins like <a href=\"https://optinmonster.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">OptinMonster</a>and <a href=\"https://wpforms.com\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">WP forms</a>, so you can send emails to the subscriber lists created with these plugins with ease.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">5. Yoast SEO</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-154146\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/yoast-seo-best-free-wordpress-seo-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"yoast-seo-best-free-wordpress-seo-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"182\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/yoast-seo-best-free-wordpress-seo-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/yoast-seo-best-free-wordpress-seo-plugin-300x98.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p>SEO is one of the most important factors affecting your business growth. Simply put: when your site gets a better ranking on search engines, you&#8217;ll get more organic traffic and more customers.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/wordpress-seo/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Yoast SEO</a> is the best SEO plugin for WordPress. It helps you to optimize your WordPress website for search engines with a set of powerful features.</p>\n<p>The Yoast SEO plugin allows you to set a focused keyword for your blog posts and then analyses your content to check whether your content is well-optimized or not. Then, it shows you the analysis and offers suggestions to make improvements, if necessary. In addition, it offers more amazing SEO features like XML sitemaps, breadcrumbs, robots control, automatic internal linking, and much more.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/sucuri/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">6. Sucuri</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/sucuri/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155274\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/sucuri-wordpress-security.jpg\" alt=\"sucuri-wordpress-security\" width=\"560\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/sucuri-wordpress-security.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/sucuri-wordpress-security-300x139.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/sucuri/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Sucuri</a> is one of the most widely-used website security platforms on the market. It offers security solutions to websites run on CMS platforms like WordPress, Joomla, Drupal, Magento, etc.</p>\n<p>Sucuris security service includes protection and quick recovery from website hacks, DDoS attacks, Blacklist warnings, etc. It also helps to prevent security issues by constantly monitoring your site against threats.</p>\n<p>In addition, it features website backups, performance optimization, quick threat alerts, and a dedicated support from an expert team. Sucuri takes care of your website security entirely.</p>\n<p>Sucuri offers a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/sucuri-scanner/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">free plugin</a> for basic website protection.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/w3-total-cache/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">7. W3 Total Cache</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/w3-total-cache/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-154149\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/w3-total-cache-free-wp-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"w3-total-cache-free-wp-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"182\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/w3-total-cache-free-wp-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/w3-total-cache-free-wp-plugin-300x98.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Speed optimization is necessary for all types of websites. Enhanced website speed helps you to improve your search engine rankings as its an important ranking factor for Google. Plus, you can ensure more happy users by offering a fast-loading website.</p>\n<p>Caching plays a vital role in improving WordPress speed. So, <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/w3-total-cache/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">W3 Total Cache</a> is a must-have plugin for all WordPress sites. Its the best WordPress caching plugin out there. It creates a cache for every part of your WordPress site and improves your server&#8217;s performance.</p>\n<p>In addition, W3 Total Cache offers a CDN module to help you easily integrate your site with content delivery networks (CDNs).</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/backupbuddy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">8. BackupBuddy</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/backupbuddy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155275\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/backupbuddy-wordpress-backup-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"backupbuddy-wordpress-backup-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/backupbuddy-wordpress-backup-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/backupbuddy-wordpress-backup-plugin-300x139.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p>Although you may use the best security measures, there can be loopholes sometimes where hackers and spambots can attack. Such an attack can sometimes result in the loss of your entire database and files. However, you can recover your site if you have a backup.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/backupbuddy\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">BackupBuddy</a> helps you to create complete backups for your WordPress website. Plus, it helps you to easily schedule automatic backups, store your backups to the Cloud, restore, and migrate your site with the backup files. In addition, you can perform quick malware scans and avoid security issues on your site.</p>\n<p>BackupBuddy will send you instant email notifications after it finishes its tasks so you can always be sure that you have the latest backup of your site.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">9. MemberPress</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155276\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/memberpress-wordpress-membership-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"memberpress-wordpress-membership-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/memberpress-wordpress-membership-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/memberpress-wordpress-membership-plugin-300x139.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p>If you have unique and useful content, you can turn your website into a membership site and earn recurring income by selling memberships. <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/memberpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">MemberPress</a> is the best WordPress membership plugin because it enables you to turn your normal business site into a full-fledged membership site.</p>\n<p>Using this plugin, you can easily create multiple membership plans and specify what content to provide per access level. Then, you can sell the memberships and make your premium content accessible only to those who subscribed to one of your memberships.</p>\n<p>MemberPress has built-in integration with the most popular payment gateways including Stripe, PayPal, etc. so that accepting payments is easy. In addition, it has integration with many other third-party tools such as email marketing software, affiliate software, podcasting, etc. to help you add more power to your site.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://enviragallery.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">10. Envira Gallery</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://enviragallery.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155277\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/envira-gallery-wordpress-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"envira-gallery-wordpress-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/envira-gallery-wordpress-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/envira-gallery-wordpress-plugin-300x139.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://enviragallery.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Envira Gallery</a> is the best responsive image gallery plugin for WordPress. It helps you to create stunning image and video galleries, as well as albums, on your WordPress site with ease.</p>\n<p>Envira Gallery plugin comes with a simple drag and drop builder which you can use to create beautiful photo and video galleries in just a few clicks. Therere dozens of pre-built templates available that you can use to customize the appearance of your galleries.</p>\n<p>When you have a really impressive portfolio section on your business site, therere increased chances for receiving more paid projects.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/learndash/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">11. LearnDash</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/learndash/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155278\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/learndash-lms-software.jpg\" alt=\"learndash-lms-software\" width=\"560\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/learndash-lms-software.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/learndash-lms-software-300x139.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/learndash/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">LearnDash</a> is the best learning management system (LMS) available on the market. Its used by hundreds of the worlds largest companies, major universities, training organizations, and entrepreneurs for creating and selling their online courses.</p>\n<p>Using LearnDash, you can create and sell online courses from your WordPress website easily. It comes with a full set of powerful features for creating full-fledged online courses. Some of its major features are drip feed content to automatically deliver content in a predefined date, reward options to deliver certificates, points to the learners, and engagement triggers to interact with users based on their actions on your site.</p>\n<p>On top of everything, it offers a very simple interface which you can configure and use fully without any coding skills.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">12. ThirstyAffiliates</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-154166\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-free-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"thirstyaffiliates-free-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"182\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-free-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/thirstyaffiliates-free-plugin-300x98.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p>You can earn a good amount of affiliate income by adding affiliate links on your business website. <a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">ThirstyAffiliates</a> provides you with an easy solution to add affiliate links in WordPress.</p>\n<p>ThirstyAffiliates is the best and most user-friendly WordPress affiliate management plugin available on the market. The plugin allows you to cloak long and ugly affiliate links by turning them into short URLs, and helps you to add them into your blog posts easily.</p>\n<p>Plus, it has automatic 404 checker so that you&#8217;ll never miss an affiliate link 404 error. It also has a <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/thirstyaffiliates/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">lite version</a> for basic users.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/css-hero/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"> 13. CSS Hero</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/css-hero/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155280\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/css-hero-wordpress-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"css-hero-wordpress-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/css-hero-wordpress-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/css-hero-wordpress-plugin-300x150.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/css-hero/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">CSS Hero</a> is an amazing WordPress plugin for improving your WordPress design. It enables you to customize your WordPress themes easily without touching any code. You can edit your entire website design live, from the front end.</p>\n<p>Using this plugin, you can fully edit your website typography, color management, and more. Plus, you can edit and control your site responsively for different devices separately to make sure your design looks great on all devices.</p>\n<p>CSS Hero has in-built integration with the image repository UnSplash so that you have direct access to the high-quality copyright-free images.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/beaver-builder/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">14. Beaver Builder</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/beaver-builder/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155281\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/beaver-builder-wordpress-page-builder.jpg\" alt=\"beaver-builder-wordpress-page-builder\" width=\"560\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/beaver-builder-wordpress-page-builder.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/beaver-builder-wordpress-page-builder-300x150.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/beaver-builder/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Beaver Builder</a>is the best WordPress page builder plugin for creating beautiful landing pages. With this plugin, you can build high converting landing pages in a matter of minutes simply by dragging and dropping.</p>\n<p>To help you quick-start creating a landing page, it offers dozens of gorgeous page templates. You can pick one of them, customize it with your own content, and publish it. You can edit your page entirely from the front end with its visual drag and drop interface.</p>\n<p>This plugin is helpful if you have multiple products on your site and want to showcase them beautifully. The plugin is a free premium plugin so you can use its <a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/beaver-builder-lite-version/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">free version</a> before making a purchase decision.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/google-apps-work/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">15. G Suite (Formerly Google Apps for Work)</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/google-apps-work/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155282\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/gsuite-gmail-for-business.jpg\" alt=\"gsuite-gmail-for-business\" width=\"560\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/gsuite-gmail-for-business.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/gsuite-gmail-for-business-300x150.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/google-apps-work/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">G Suite</a> is a very important service every business website needs. It provides powerful and secure business emails for your website. With a professional email, you can make illicit more efficient communication within your team as well as with your business partners.</p>\n<p>G Suite is the professional email hosting service from the Google. It comes with many benefits other than just a professional email, like integration with online calendars, online documents, video conferencing, etc.</p>\n<p>G Suite is an easier business email solution because it looks more like your personal Gmail account. In addition, security is another major factor for choosing G Suite versus other email hosting services.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">16. SEMRush</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155283\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/semrush-marketing-tool.jpg\" alt=\"semrush-marketing-tool\" width=\"560\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/semrush-marketing-tool.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/semrush-marketing-tool-300x150.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/semrush/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">SEMRush</a> is a powerful marketing toolkit for digital marketing professionals as well as business site owners. Using SEMRush, you can get insights into your competitors strategies in organic and paid search, link building, advertising, etc. with which you can improve your marketing strategies.</p>\n<p>More specifically, you can see your competitors best keywords, advertising strategies, and budget, their top authority backlinks, etc. Plus, it shows keyword difficulty score for each of the keywords so that you can decide which keywords are likely to offer you a better position in search results.</p>\n<p>SEMRush offers more features including site audit, social media tracker, content analyzer, PPC keyword tool etc. Its a great tool for every business with a goal to scale higher.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/livechat/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">17. LiveChat</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/livechat/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155284\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/live-chat-software.jpg\" alt=\"live-chat-software\" width=\"560\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/live-chat-software.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/live-chat-software-300x139.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/livechat/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">LiveChat</a> makes it easy to add a live chat feature on your business sites and offer customer support instantly. Its a powerful live chat software you can use.</p>\n<p>Using this software, you can easily set up live chat on your business website with just a few steps. Once its set up, you can help your users with real-time responses to their queries.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/insert-headers-and-footers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">18. Insert Headers and Footers</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/insert-headers-and-footers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-154153\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/insert-headers-and-footers-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"insert-headers-and-footers-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"182\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/insert-headers-and-footers-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/insert-headers-and-footers-plugin-300x98.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/insert-headers-and-footers/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Insert Headers and Footers</a> is a really useful plugin for business owners with few-to-no coding skills because it helps you to add code to your themes header or footer area easily without actually having to learn how to code.</p>\n<p>Sometimes, you may need to add codes such as Google Analytics&#8217; tracking code, meta verification, custom CSS, etc. to your themes header or footer area. But, to edit your themes header.php and footer.php file, you&#8217;d need to have good coding skills. Plus, it can be risky to make changes to these files.</p>\n<p>Insert Headers and Footers plugin saves you from all that. Another benefit of using this plugin is that your Google Analytics tracking code will not be lost, even if you change your theme.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/soliloquy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">19. Soliloquy</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/soliloquy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155285\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/soliloquy-best-wordpress-slider-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"soliloquy-best-wordpress-slider-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/soliloquy-best-wordpress-slider-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/soliloquy-best-wordpress-slider-plugin-300x150.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/soliloquy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Soliloquy</a> is the best WordPress slider plugin that lets you create stunning sliders for your business website in just a few clicks. It comes with an easy-to-use drag and drop interface for building image and video sliders. Its fully responsive so that your sliders will look great on all types of devices irrespective of the screen size and resolution.</p>\n<p>Soliloquy comes with a number of beautiful slider templates that you can use to build sliders instantly. For a WooCommerce store, it also has a product slider option.</p>\n<p>Plus, it features fullscreen lightbox, dynamic sliders, SEO and performance optimized, integration with powerful third party tools, and much more.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/woocommerce/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">20. WooCommerce</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/woocommerce/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155286\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/woocommerce-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"woocommerce-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"260\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/woocommerce-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/woocommerce-plugin-300x139.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/woocommerce/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"> WooCommerce</a> is the official eCommerce plugin for WordPress. It enables you to sell digital as well as physical products from your WordPress site. Its useful for you if you want to sell anything from your business site.</p>\n<p>You can download the WooCommerce core plugin from WordPreess.org; however, it has limited options for a full-fledged eCommerce site. You can use its premium extensions for advanced features.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/birchpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">21. BirchPress</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/birchpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155287\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/birchpress-wordpress-appointment-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"birchpress-wordpress-appointment-plugin\" width=\"560\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/birchpress-wordpress-appointment-plugin.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/birchpress-wordpress-appointment-plugin-300x150.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/birchpress/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">BirchPress</a> is a premium WordPress appointment booking plugin that helps you to add online booking forms on your WordPress website. This is especially useful if you have a service-related business like a hotel, restaurant, dental office, etc.</p>\n<p>By adding an online booking form, you can allow your website visitors to book appointments for your services in advance. This helps you to manage your teams work schedule in a more organized manner.</p>\n<p>BirchPress is a powerful plugin that helps you to create booking forms, schedule booking, and accept payments online.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/slack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">22. Slack</a></h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/slack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-155288\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/slack-team-management-software.jpg\" alt=\"slack-team-management-software\" width=\"560\" height=\"280\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/slack-team-management-software.jpg 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/slack-team-management-software-300x150.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.wpbeginner.com/refer/slack/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Slack</a> is a powerful team management and communication tool useful for business websites. If you have a team working in different geographical locations, it provides a really simple and effective way to communicate with your team. We use it ourselves!</p>\n<p>Slack has over 1000 install-ready apps including G Suite, Dropbox, Salesforce, and many more so you can enhance your workflow significantly.</p>\n<p>We hope this article helped you find the best WordPress plugins for your business website. You may also like to check out our guide on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/reasons-why-website-analytics-is-important-for-your-business-growth/\">why website analytics are important for your business growth</a>.</p>\n<p>Also, dont forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Facebook</a> for more WordPress and Google Analytics tutorials.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/must-have-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-business-websites/\">22 Must Have WordPress Plugins and Tools for Business Websites (2018)</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:97:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/must-have-wordpress-plugins-and-tools-for-business-websites/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}i:9;a:6:{s:4:\"data\";s:51:\"\n		\n		\n		\n		\n		\n				\n		\n		\n		\n\n		\n		\n				\n			\n		\n		\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";s:5:\"child\";a:5:{s:0:\"\";a:7:{s:5:\"title\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:96:\"MonsterInsights vs. Google Analyticator  Which is the Best WordPress Google Analytics Plugin?\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:257:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/monsterinsights-vs-google-analyticator-which-is-the-best-wordpress-google-analytics-plugin/?utm_source=rss&utm_medium=rss&utm_campaign=monsterinsights-vs-google-analyticator-which-is-the-best-wordpress-google-analytics-plugin\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:131:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/monsterinsights-vs-google-analyticator-which-is-the-best-wordpress-google-analytics-plugin/#respond\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:7:\"pubDate\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:31:\"Mon, 27 Aug 2018 13:15:27 +0000\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:8:\"category\";a:4:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:9:\"Marketing\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:1;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:45:\"best WordPress Google Analytics plugin review\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:2;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:35:\"Google Analytics plugins comparison\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}i:3;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:22:\"MonsterInsights review\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:4:\"guid\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:41:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/?p=157367\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{s:0:\"\";a:1:{s:11:\"isPermaLink\";s:5:\"false\";}}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}s:11:\"description\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:731:\"<p>Wondering which website analytics tool to use in your WordPress site? If you want a simple-yet-powerful solution, you can use a plugin like MonsterInsights or Google Analyticator. Both of these plugins connect your WordPress site with Google Analytics to provide you with site metrics; however, therere some big differences in the way they work. In [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/monsterinsights-vs-google-analyticator-which-is-the-best-wordpress-google-analytics-plugin/\">MonsterInsights vs. Google Analyticator  Which is the Best WordPress Google Analytics Plugin?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:32:\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\";a:1:{s:7:\"creator\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:10:\"Sunita Rai\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:40:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\";a:1:{s:7:\"encoded\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:24166:\"<p>Wondering which website analytics tool to use in your WordPress site? If you want a simple-yet-powerful solution, you can use a plugin like MonsterInsights or Google Analyticator. Both of these plugins connect your WordPress site with Google Analytics to provide you with site metrics; however, therere some big differences in the way they work.</p>\n<p>In this article, well compare MonsterInsights vs. Google Analyticator and show you the major differences that matter.</p>\n<h3>1. General Overview: MonsterInsights vs. Google Analyticator</h3>\n<h4>Whats MonsterInsights?</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157422\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress.jpg\" alt=\"monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress\" width=\"620\" height=\"250\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-best-ga-plugin-for-wordpress-300x121.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> is the most user-friendly, most powerful, Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. It helps you to easily integrate Google Analytics into your WordPress site and provides you with detailed information and stats about your site visitors and their interactions with your site.</p>\n<p>MonsterInsights simplifies the entire process of using Google Analytics and empowers everyone who uses it, including beginners. Youll see not only the regular site metrics that Google Analytics offers by default, but also sophisticated metrics like <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/ecommerce/\">eCommerce</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/ads/\">ads</a>, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/forms/\">forms</a>, etc.</p>\n<p>Another plus point is that you can view all of these reports in your WordPress dashboard. It includes a <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/feature/google-analytics-dashboard/\">dashboard widget</a> to show your website overview report and a <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/your-ultimate-guide-to-monsterinsights-dashboard-reports/\">report page</a> to let you view the complete report.</p>\n<p>In addition, it also provides you with a link to the Google Analytics website to view the full report. Its especially useful to the people who want to use Google Analytics, but have no idea how to configure its settings and view reports.</p>\n<h4>Whats Google Analyticator?</h4>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/google-analyticator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157423\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/g-analyticator-wordpress-plugin.jpg\" alt=\"g-analyticator-wordpress-plugin\" width=\"620\" height=\"200\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/g-analyticator-wordpress-plugin.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/g-analyticator-wordpress-plugin-300x97.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></a></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://wordpress.org/plugins/google-analyticator/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Google Analyticator</a> is another simple Google Analytics plugin for WordPress. Like MonsterInsights, it helps you with an easy installation of Google Analytics code on your site without having to edit your theme file to insert the code.</p>\n<p>Another similarity of the plugin with MonsterInsights is reporting via a dashboard widget. The dashboard widget lets you view your sites performance at a glance right in your dashboard (yoursite.com/wp-admin).</p>\n<p>The dashboard widget shows you a quick summary of your website analytics report, but its limited. MonsterInsights, in contrast, has a well-designed and comprehensive report page inside your dashboard where you can view all the standard Google Analytics reports as well as advanced metrics.</p>\n<h3>2. Reporting: Basic Overview vs. Advanced Metrics</h3>\n<p>The major difference between MonsterInsights and Google Analyticator is reporting features. Google Analyticator shows only the basic overview of your site&#8217;s performance whereas MonsterInsights provides you with advanced metrics in the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/your-ultimate-guide-to-monsterinsights-dashboard-reports/\">Reports</a> page along with the dashboard widget.</p>\n<p>Google Analyticator&#8217;s dashboard widget looks like the screenshot below:</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157425\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/google-analyticator-dashboard-report.jpg\" alt=\"google-analyticator-dashboard-report\" width=\"620\" height=\"441\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/google-analyticator-dashboard-report.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/google-analyticator-dashboard-report-300x213.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>It includes the following reports:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>A graph showing the unique sessions your site triggered in past 30 days (the dashboard widget shows 30 days by default which you can change into yesterday or 60 days).</li>\n<li>A quick summary of site usage: total visits, pageviews, pages per visit, bounce rate, average time on site, and percent of new visits</li>\n<li>Top 5 referrers to your website</li>\n<li>Top search terms used to find you website</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Thats all the Google Analyticator plugin shows you by default. You can add a few other reports to it by enabling tracking features in its setting page. To configure its settings, you&#8217;ll need to navigate to <strong>Google Analytics  Google Analytics</strong> from your WordPress dashboard.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157430\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/g-analyticator-settings.jpg\" alt=\"g-analyticator-settings\" width=\"620\" height=\"441\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/g-analyticator-settings.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/g-analyticator-settings-300x213.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>From here, you can enable a few tracking options, as listed below:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Outbound link tracking</li>\n<li>Event tracking  if enabled, outbound links and downloads are treated as events instead of pageviews</li>\n<li>Enhanced link attribution  if youve 2 or more links to the same destination from one page, this feature will show you which link is getting more clicks</li>\n<li>Downloads tracking  if youve downloadable files such as pdf, MP3, etc.</li>\n<li>Google Adsense tracking</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Thats all. There arent any more tracking options in the Google Analyticator.</p>\n<p>Now, lets go ahead and check the reporting options in MonsterInsights.</p>\n<p>First, heres what the<a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/introducing-google-analytics-dashboard-widget-for-monsterinsights/\">MonsterInsights dashboard widget</a> lets you see:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Overview report  a graph showing your sites unique pageviews in 30 days and quick summary of total sessions, pageviews, average session duration, and bounce rate.</li>\n<li>Top 10 posts/ pages for your site with a link to Google Analytics site to view more than 10 pages. (Google Analyticator shows only 5 top pages)</li>\n<li>New vs. returning visitors  pie chart presentation in percent</li>\n<li>Device breakdown  percent of users on desktop, tablet and mobile with a pie chart</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-154759\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/monsterinsightsdashboardwidget.png\" alt=\"Google Analytics Dashboard Widget for WordPress by MonsterInsights\" width=\"620\" height=\"420\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/monsterinsightsdashboardwidget.png 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/02/monsterinsightsdashboardwidget-300x203.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>The MonsterInsights dashboard widget lets you have a quick glance of your sites overview report.</p>\n<p>To view all the other reports, you need to go the <strong>Insights  Reports</strong> from your admin panel. Now, lets see what MonsterInsights reports show you:</p>\n<h4>i) Overview Report</h4>\n<p>At first, youll see the <strong>Overview Report</strong> of which most of the reports are available in the dashboard widget. It has <strong>Pageviews</strong> in the graphical presentation added. And, top 10 countries from where users are coming to your site.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157435\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-overview-report.jpg\" alt=\"monsterinsights-overview-report\" width=\"620\" height=\"575\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-overview-report.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-overview-report-300x278.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<h4>ii) Publishers Report</h4>\n<p>Next to <strong>Overview</strong> tab in MonsterInsights reports is <strong>Publishers</strong>. Click on the tab to see the following data:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Top Landing Pages</li>\n<li>Exit Pages</li>\n<li>Outbound Links</li>\n<li>Affiliate Links</li>\n<li>Download Links</li>\n<li>Demographics</li>\n<li>Interest Categories</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Publishers report has a lot of information helpful for bloggers and digital marketers.</p>\n<p>First, can see the top 10 landing pages on your site with the number of visits, average duration on the page, and bounce rate. This report is helpful for analyzing the performance of your webpages individually. Google Analyticator misses out such detailed information for your top pages.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-148181\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Publishers-Report-Top-Landing-Pages.png\" alt=\"Publishers Report Top Landing Pages\" width=\"560\" height=\"399\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Publishers-Report-Top-Landing-Pages.png 560w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/06/Publishers-Report-Top-Landing-Pages-300x214.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 560px) 100vw, 560px\" /></p>\n<p>Second, you can see the top exit pages with the total number of exits, page views and percent of exits. This report is not available in Google Analyticator.</p>\n<p>Third, you can see the top outbound links on your site. This feature is also available in Google Analyticator.</p>\n<p>Fourth, you can see the top affiliate links in your site. If youve added affiliate links on your site, then the plugin tracks which affiliate links are getting most clicks and show you the reports in <strong>Publishers</strong> report. Google Analyticator doesnt have this feature.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157438\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/affiliate-links-tracking-monsterinsights.jpg\" alt=\"Affiliate-Links-Tracking-MonsterInsights\" width=\"620\" height=\"700\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/affiliate-links-tracking-monsterinsights.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/affiliate-links-tracking-monsterinsights-266x300.jpg 266w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>Fifth, you can find top download links, demographic and interest categories reports. These reports can be tracked in Google Analyticator as well.</p>\n<p>If you want more comprehensive data than what the Publishers Report offers, you can always check out our <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-definitive-guide-to-google-analytics-for-publishers/\">definitive guide to Google Analytics for publishers</a>.</p>\n<h4>iii) eCommerce Report</h4>\n<p>Click on the <strong>eCommerce</strong> tab in MonsterInsights to get a quick glance at how your online shop is doing.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/ecommerce/\">eCommerce tracking</a> is yet another great feature youll find in MonsterInsights, but not in Google Analyticator. While eCommerce tracking setup in the standard Google Analytics platform is complicated, MonsterInsights makes it very simple that itll require just a few clicks.</p>\n<p>In the first section, youll see a quick summary of your shops conversion rate, total transactions, total revenue generated, and average order value. Then, therere your top 50 products with the total number of sales, percent of sales, and total revenue generated by each product.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-119424\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mi-ecommerce-report.jpg\" alt=\"eCommerce reporting in WordPress\" width=\"600\" height=\"390\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mi-ecommerce-report.jpg 600w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/mi-ecommerce-report-300x195.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<p>You can also check out how many days it took for site visitors to make a purchase from your website. This includes the number of transactions that were actually finalized.</p>\n<p>In addition, you&#8217;ll see how many sessions it took site visitors to make a purchase. Plus, view how many transactions were finalized, and the total percentage.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-119419\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopper-behavior.jpg\" alt=\"Shopper behavior in WordPress\" width=\"600\" height=\"345\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopper-behavior.jpg 600w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/12/shopper-behavior-300x173.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 600px) 100vw, 600px\" /></p>\n<p>For help with boosting sales in your eCommerce shop, be sure to check out these <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/smart-tactics-to-reduce-shopping-cart-abandonment/\">11 smart tactics for reducing shopping cart abandonment</a>.</p>\n<h4>iv) Search Console Report</h4>\n<p>MonsterInsights lets you view your Google Search Console report inside your WordPress dashboard. First, youll need to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/docs/how-to-connect-google-search-console-to-google-analytics/\">connect your Search Console account to Google Analytics</a> to view this report.</p>\n<p>Once its set up, click on the <strong>Search Console Report</strong> tab to find out your Top 50 Google Search Terms.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157448\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-search-console-report.jpg\" alt=\"monsterinsights-search-console-report\" width=\"620\" height=\"636\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-search-console-report.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/monsterinsights-search-console-report-292x300.jpg 292w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>As you can see in the screenshot, youll see the following after each term:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Clicks</li>\n<li>Impressions</li>\n<li>Click-Through Rate</li>\n<li>Average Position</li>\n</ul>\n<p>This gives you a good idea of the keywords that are bringing people to your website. Plus, it helps you see whether people are finding what theyre looking for once on your site. This information is useful for <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/how-to-improve-your-keyword-research-to-boost-traffic-and-sales/\">improving your keyword research</a> to boost traffic and sales.</p>\n<p>Google Analyticator plugin also shows your sites top searches, but it shows you only 5 terms. And, you can see only the number of clicks for each term. Its much more detailed in MosterInsights&#8217; reports.</p>\n<h4>v) Custom Dimensions Report</h4>\n<p>The fifth tab in the MonsterInsights reports is <strong>Custom Dimensions</strong>. On clicking the tab, you can following reports in it:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Which authors posts generate the most traffic</li>\n<li>The keywords youre using and which ones are doing well in search engines</li>\n<li>SEO score tracking to see which blog SEO scores are the most popular</li>\n<li>Which categories on your site are clicked the most</li>\n<li>Which custom post types are the most well-liked by site visitors</li>\n</ul>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157455\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/most-popular-authors-custom-dimensions-report-monsterinsights.jpg\" alt=\"Most-Popular-Authors-Custom-Dimensions-Report-Monsterinsights\" width=\"620\" height=\"579\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/most-popular-authors-custom-dimensions-report-monsterinsights.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/most-popular-authors-custom-dimensions-report-monsterinsights-300x280.jpg 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>MonsterInsights makes it easy to <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/the-beginners-guide-to-custom-dimensions-in-google-analytics/\">set up tracking for custom dimensions</a>. Its quite tricky in the standard Google Analytics. And, you cant find this option in Google Analyticator.</p>\n<h4>vi) Forms Tracking Report</h4>\n<p>Another very important tracking feature in MonsterInsights is <strong>forms tracking</strong>. You can find the forms report by clicking the <strong>Forms</strong> tab in MonsterInsights report page.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-157484\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/forms-report-monsterinsights.jpg\" alt=\"forms-report-monsterinsights\" width=\"620\" height=\"630\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/forms-report-monsterinsights.jpg 620w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2018/08/forms-report-monsterinsights-295x300.jpg 295w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px\" /></p>\n<p>As you can see in the screenshot above, it shows you the total impressions, conversions, and conversion rate for each of your forms.</p>\n<p>Forms tracking in the standard Google Analytics platform requires you set up event tracking, but its automated in MonsterInsights. This feature isnt available in the Google Analyticator plugin.</p>\n<p>That&#8217;s about it for what aspects <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> can track. Now, let&#8217;s see which plugin is more accurate and optimization-ready.</p>\n<h3>3. Accurate Tracking and Optimization</h3>\n<p>Both MonsterInsights and Google Analyticator connect Google Analytics for your WordPress site&#8217;s metrics; however, MonsterInsights is more accurate with its power addons.</p>\n<p>For example, if you&#8217;ve enabled Google AMP, it can boost your mobile rankings, but it can skew mobile analytics. While the standard Google Analytics script fails to track the AMP visitors accurately, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/amp/\">MonsterInsights&#8217; AMP addon</a> adds helps to track them accurately.</p>\n<p>Another addon <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/performance/\">MonsterInsights Performance addon</a> helps you to adjust site speed and sample rate for Google Analytics. If youre running a high traffic site, you may hit the Google Analytics processing limit. So this addon helps you to stay within its limit by allowing you to specify what percentage of users should be tracked.</p>\n<p><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-89772\" src=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/performance-addon-screenshot.png\" alt=\"performance addon options\" width=\"540\" height=\"448\" srcset=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/performance-addon-screenshot.png 540w, https://www.monsterinsights.com/wp-content/uploads/2017/02/performance-addon-screenshot-300x249.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 540px) 100vw, 540px\" /></p>\n<p>Furthermore, MonsterInsights lets you use split testing and personalization with its <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/google-optimize/\">Google Optimize addon</a>. The addon helps you to connect your Google Optimize account with Analytics and lets you use your Analytics data to conduct A/B tests and improve user experience and conversions.</p>\n<p>Plus, it features easy <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/facebook-instant-articles/\">integration with Facebook Instant Articles</a> and insights on your Facebook audience.</p>\n<p>You can explore more on <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/features/\">MonsterInsights features</a>.</p>\n<h3>4. Google Analyticator vs. MonsterInsights  Which Plugin Should You Use?</h3>\n<p>After our review of all the reporting options these 2 plugins offer, it&#8217;s probably obvious which plugin you should use.</p>\n<p>But if youre still wondering, heres the checklist for you to review these 2 plugins once again.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Reporting Options</strong>: MonsterInsights is clearly the WINNER as it allows you to track advanced analytics metrics and shows you the reports inside your WordPress dashboard. Google Analyticator provides you only the basic overview of your site analytics in the dashboard widget.</li>\n<li><strong>Ease of Use</strong>: Both MonsterInsights and Google Analyticator are easy to use; easy installation of Google Analytics code and dashboard widget to view reports directly.</li>\n<li><strong>Plugin Settings</strong>: Both the plugins settings are quite simple. Therere more settings in MonsterInsights but theyre beautifully crafted and well-designed.</li>\n<li><strong>Data Accuracy</strong>: MonsterInsights has powerful addons like <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/amp/\">Google AMP</a> and <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/addon/performance/\">Performance addon</a> to ensure data accuracy.</li>\n<li><strong>Tutorials and resources</strong>: If youre stuck at any point while using MonsterInsights, you can check out its <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/docs/\">documentation</a>. It has highly comprehensive articles to help you out. Additionally, you can also find resources in the <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/blog/\">MonsterInsights</a> blog but its hard to find such tutorials and resources for Google Analyticator.</li>\n<li><strong>Support and future updates</strong>: Similarly, MonsterInsights users can get fully dedicated support from its expert team but youll need to depend mostly on the support forum for Google Analyticator support. Since the company has other products in priority, their support isnt dedicated like that of MonsterInsiights.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Without a doubt, <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/\">MonsterInsights</a> is the plugin youll need to install in WordPress to track your website analytics entirely. Its advanced tracking features and easy to use interface make it the best Google Analytics plugin for WordPress.</p>\n<p>So, what are you waiting for? Get started with <a href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/pricing/\">MonsterInsights</a> today and track how your site is performing with ease.</p>\n<p>And dont forget to follow us on <a href=\"https://twitter.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Twitter</a> and <a href=\"https://www.facebook.com/monsterinsights\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener\">Facebook</a> for more helpful Google Analytics tips.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/monsterinsights-vs-google-analyticator-which-is-the-best-wordpress-google-analytics-plugin/\">MonsterInsights vs. Google Analyticator  Which is the Best WordPress Google Analytics Plugin?</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.monsterinsights.com\">MonsterInsights</a>.</p>\n\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:36:\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\";a:1:{s:10:\"commentRss\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:128:\"https://www.monsterinsights.com/monsterinsights-vs-google-analyticator-which-is-the-best-wordpress-google-analytics-plugin/feed/\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}s:38:\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\";a:1:{s:8:\"comments\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:1:\"0\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:0:{}s:8:\"xml_base\";s:0:\"\";s:17:\"xml_base_explicit\";b:0;s:8:\"xml_lang\";s:0:\"\";}}}}}}}s:27:\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\";a:1:{s:4:\"link\";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:\"data\";s:0:\"\";s:7:\"attribs\";a:1:{