(466, 2, '2018-09-19 19:54:33', '2018-09-19 19:54:33', '<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">In a series of tweets, beauty vlogger Mae Layug expressed her support to stop cosmetic animal testing by deleting almost 40 of her product reviews on brand involved in this practice.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-467\" src=\"http://page5.ph/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/pasted-image-0.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"663\" />\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Layug also mentioned dropping deals and partnerships with popular brands such as Loreal, Maybelline, Estee Lauder, Revlon, Mary Kay, Nars, and Avon as they are known for testing their products on animals.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Instead, she encouraged everyone to switch and use cruelty-free products from brands like Wet N wild, ELF, Catrice, Colourpop, Makeup Revolution, L.A. Girl.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Locally, Ever Bilena, Careline, Blk Cosmetics, Vice Cosmetics.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Each year, hundreds of thousands of animals in the world are used and killed just to assess the safety of cosmetics.</span>\r\n\r\n<span style=\"font-weight: 400;\">Layug ended the thread by encouraging everyone to participate in a petition that would ban animal testing worldwide.</span>\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-469\" src=\"http://page5.ph/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/pasted-image-0-1.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"843\" />\r\n\r\n<img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-470\" src=\"http://page5.ph/wp-content/uploads/2018/09/pasted-image-0-2.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"750\" height=\"843\" />', 'Mae Layug promotes cruelty-free beauty', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'mae-layug-promotes-cruelty-free-beauty', '', '', '2018-09-27 00:43:59', '2018-09-26 16:43:59', '', 0, 'http://page5.ph/?p=466', 0, 'post', '', 0),
