(563, 3, '2018-09-27 12:00:28', '2018-09-27 04:00:28', '<p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c0\">Youtube content creator Sheks Diary addresses apology and clarification on the issue of insensitivity towards the marginalized sector.\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c0\">In one of her tweets, the 22-year old influencer made a remark on the poor people that sparked controversy in the internet.\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><img title=\"\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/RjfHDnbvJ48S15sMVoKZ7DpDP0kVsJ7Z96FRaYiyKt3k25oQARv0qqc8s7jj_ynnmYfvO7ONJOflqJikK8hOfXEXvSSlZpSn1pEJSI27NvFv6Xn5BAFiWrehMr0PkEf3-5PuC1Vl\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c3 c6\">Bakit ba may thinking sa Pinas na kapag may pera ka, obligasyon mo tumulong sa mahirap?\r\nSorry pero pet-peeve ko yung mga pabuhat. Hindi ko ugaling tumulong sa mahirap kasi pinalaki akong tinuturuan paano magisda kesa humingi ng isda so yun icocontribute ko.\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c0\">One twitter user with the account handle @RoyalsMiggy expressed his frustration and disappointment towards Sheks Diary while tagging her as a Toxic Youtuber.\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><img title=\"\" src=\"https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/uPhDhpx3QciY_3swS24IL2dXNO00Ldfsw4wuT4rRhSK_uQPDY4YhHRJZP5iaPznzFPdCkJW2wiZ_HSMAHpleqwkit5zgO6MMvONZ6BS3_Zx0_Z9BOqPGb6tyMuMTG9HC_rs7y-T6\" alt=\"\" /></p>\r\n<p class=\"c2\">Shek then issued an immediate public apology on the issue through one of her latest vlogs in her Youtube channel  <span class=\"c5 c4\">Reacting to Harsh Comments. Tea?\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c3\">It was very insensitive. I wasnt able to clarify immediately. I am really really sorry sa mga taong nasaktan ko. There are times that I am a regular 22 years old girl who is just so happy, careless and never realized the impact of my influence,</span><span class=\"c0\">Shek exclaimed.\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c3\">Ang ibig sabihin ko kasi sa mga pabuhat, ay ang mga taong kapos na nga, willing kang tulungan pero choosy pa</span><span class=\"c0\">, said as she clarifies the terms pabuhat and mahirap in her tweet.\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c0\">She then expressed her admiration on people who are poor but really hardworking just make ends for their families.\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c3\">Personally I believe sa mga taong grabe kumayod everyday, na gumigising ng maaga para lang maitaguyod nila ang family nila. Thats a story really close to my heart kasi dyan din naman nagsimula ang aking mga parents,</span><span class=\"c0\">she added.</span></p>\r\n<p class=\"c2\"><span class=\"c0\">As she disclosed the issue, she shared one major lesson that she has learned from that incident - not to rant on twitter or in social media in general, considering that her influence might affect not only her career but her personal life.</span></p>', 'Shek\'s Diary Clarifies \'Insensitive\' Tweet', '', 'publish', 'open', 'open', '', 'sheks-diary-clarifies-insensitive-tweet', '', '', '2018-09-27 01:16:43', '2018-09-26 17:16:43', '', 0, 'https://page5.ph/?p=563', 0, 'post', '', 0),
